 produced 89 Olympians.\", \"from\": 547, \"to\": 621, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 588, \"end\": 590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Oklahoma\", \"score\": 0.9506045905469258, \"rank\": 0.05196209858906158, \"text\": \"OU\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Oklahoma\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/University_of_Oklahoma\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A former or current Sooner has competed in the last 22 Olympic Games.\\u00c2  Here\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s a closer look at each Sooner competing in Paris.\\u00c2  At 33, this is Ancer\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s second time representing Mexico at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 622, \"to\": 827, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 804, \"end\": 810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.983909870297028, \"rank\": 0.010996177377838019, \"text\": \"Mexico\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He also competed at the Tokyo Olympics in 2021.\", \"from\": 828, \"to\": 875, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Although born in McAllen, TX, Ancer spent time in Reynosa, Mexico while growing up and has dual citizenship.\\u00c2  After a one-year stint at Odessa College, Ancer transferred to OU, where he graduated in 2013.\", \"from\": 876, \"to\": 1081, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 893, \"end\": 904, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McAllen,_Texas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"McAllen, TX\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McAllen,_Texas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McAllen,_Texas\"}, {\"begin\": 893, \"end\": 904, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McAllen,_Texas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"McAllen, TX\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McAllen,_Texas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/McAllen,_Texas\"}, {\"begin\": 926, \"end\": 933, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reynosa\", \"score\": 0.9999999999918145, \"rank\": 5.750219145046536e-12, \"text\": \"Reynosa\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reynosa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reynosa\"}, {\"begin\": 935, \"end\": 941, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.983909870297028, \"rank\": 0.010996177377838019, \"text\": \"Mexico\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexico_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1013, \"end\": 1027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Odessa_College\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Odessa College\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q3918\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q2385804\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Odessa_College\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Odessa_College\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ancer left Norman second all-time in scoring average in program history.\", \"from\": 1082, \"to\": 1154, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1093, \"end\": 1099, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Normandy\", \"score\": 0.9640392664771024, \"rank\": 0.03311568226762898, \"text\": \"Norman\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Normandy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Normandy\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He then started his professional career immediately and now competes on the LIV Golf Tour.\\u00c2  The men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s golf competition will start at 2 a.m. Thursday and wraps up with Round 4 on Sunday.\\u00c2  Dodanli became an Olympian before even concluding his collegiate career with OU.\", \"from\": 1155, \"to